getAsynchronousConnection

public abstract <P> ConnectionFuture<? extends C> getAsynchronousConnection(ConnectionResultHandler<? super C,P> handler,
                                                                            P p)
Initiates an asynchronous connection request to the Directory Server associated with this connection factory. The returned ConnectionFuture can be used to retrieve the completed asynchronous connection. Alternatively, if a ConnectionResultHandler is provided, the handler will be notified when the connection is available and ready for use.

Specified by:
getAsynchronousConnection in interface ConnectionFactory<C extends AsynchronousConnection>
Type Parameters:
P - The type of the additional parameter to the handler's methods.
Parameters:
handler - The completion handler, or null if no handler is to be used.
p - Optional additional handler parameter.
Returns:
A future which can be used to retrieve the asynchronous connection.

getConnection

public Connection getConnection()
                         throws ErrorResultException
Returns a connection to the Directory Server associated with this connection factory. The connection returned by this method can be used immediately.

The default implementation is to convert the asynchronous connection returned from blockingGetAsynchronousConnection() to a synchronous connection using a SynchronousConnection as per the following code: 

 return new SynchronousConnection(blockingGetAsynchronousConnection());
Implementations should override this method if they wish to return a different type of synchronous connection.

Specified by:
getConnection in interface ConnectionFactory<C extends AsynchronousConnection>
Returns:
A connection to the Directory Server associated with this connection factory.
Throws:
ErrorResultException - If the connection request failed for some reason.

blockingGetAsynchronousConnection

protected final C blockingGetAsynchronousConnection()
                                                                            throws ErrorResultException
Invokes getAsynchronousConnection, blocking until the asynchronous connection is obtained or the attempt fails.

Returns:
An asynchronous connection obtained using getAsynchronousConnection.
Throws:
ErrorResultException - If the connection request failed for some reason.
